I am a 24 year old female. Mixed, black and white. Smoker (well, vape), drink regularly, not the healthiest lifestyle. 5”5’ and 120 pounds. No history of heart conditions in my family and no pre-existing conditions. Not on any medications but quit birth control about 2 months ago after being on it for 10 years. 

I started getting weird heart palpitations last night, like a fluttering feeling and this sensation in my throat. I am used to the feeling as I have pretty severe anxiety, but typically it will go away within an hour max. But I woke up today and still had it, and have felt it until now (6:30 pm). 

No other symptoms, except that it’s triggering major anxiety. I read that my vape may be a cause and also saw that PMS (which I’m def going through right now) can cause it for whatever reason. Since I quit birth control my PMS has been hell so I feel like maybe that’s a possibility. 

I’ve never had continuous heart palpitations like this. I have extreme health anxiety so I am freaking out.

I’m also in an unfortunate position where I’ll be w/o insurance for a bit due to changing jobs. So I really want to avoid the doctor if I can. But I also don’t want to risk anything if it could be something serious.

Thanks in advance!
